# Process & environment intrinsics

R.3.4 wires `args()`, `env(name)`, and `exit(code)` to std-only
Rust helpers — no extra crate deps.

```scalascript
@main def run(): Unit =
  val greet: String = env("GREET_NAME")
  val name: String  = if (greet == "") "World" else greet
  println(s"Hello, $name")
```

Build and run:

```bash
ssc build-rust process-env.ssc
./process-env                # → Hello, World
GREET_NAME=Rust ./process-env  # → Hello, Rust
```
